Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe congratulated Donald Trump on Wednesday on his election as US president and vowed that the countries will maintain their close relationship.&#8220;I express my heartfelt congratulations on your election as the next president of the United States,&#8221; Abe said in a statement.&#8220;Japan and the United States are unshakeable allies connected by common values such as freedom, democracy, basic human rights and rule of law,&#8221; Abe added.-AFP